I was going to watch this movie because I haven't seen any new comedies lately that have been good, and Louis C.K. is in this one, but I read a little about the plot and figured he probably said yes to this movie just to appear amongst other famous names. The plot seems retarded. "Set in a world where no one can lie." Sound like a typical empty Hollywood bullshit movie, like most they produce over there. But trying to push Christianity on the public through movies isn't considered desperate and shallow in the US, so I guess such movies make millions over there. They may have all the special effects and the planet's greatest equipment stored in that particular space, but all these overproduced mainstream movies with shitty story lines, and big stars who appear in the movies only for their underwear catalog looks need to go... Think I'll watch Monty Python's Life of Brian instead. Now, there's a quality script.

OMG, ozric666: Religulous was soooo good. For the life of my I can't recall the comedians name that hosted and starred in it, but it was good. Just an account of him going around and asking religious people why they believe the way they do and challenging them with questions that any sane, free thinking person would ask in their search for clarification.

He gets a bit out of hand at times and you do not feel for when he is being thrown out of the various religious arenas, but over all...it was very cohesive.

Before people begin their bitching, The invention of lying is also very good. The subject matter was a great idea for a movie... no matter what you believe in, you have to admit this.
